<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-410] document lctl get_param for changelog size </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-410</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The latest manual discusses displaying changelog user information in&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;12.1.2.5.%C2%A0DisplayingtheChangelogIndexandRegisteredUsers&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;12.1.2.5.&#160;Displaying the Changelog Index and Registered Users&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;mdd.*.changelog_size is also important to document, since unconsumed changelogs can cause problems.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This should also include the UNITS that this changelog size is reporting. It&apos;s a number, what does that number mean? This is a pet peeve of mine with various lustre stats and numbers from lctl. Some give an xml-ish output with units, others give a number. Chaos! If units aren&apos;t included, let&apos;s document them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="52931">LUDOC-410</key>
            <summary>document lctl get_param for changelog size </summary>
